OL,3,CWhat happened at Medomsley Detention
OL,4,CCentre?
OL,6,FMedomsley Detention Centre was built
OL,7,Fin 1960 on what was formerly a
OL,8,FVictorian orphanage. It was operated
OL,9,Fby the Home Office and opened in
OL,10,FFebruary 1961.
OL,12,FIt housed offenders aged between 17
OL,13,Fand 21 on short custodial sentences to
OL,14,Fkeep them out of adult prisons and
OL,15,Faway from older criminals.
OL,17,FThe centre could house up to 130
OL,18,Fpeople but usually held around 70 at
OL,19,Fone time. Inmates tended to spend six
OL,20,Fto eight weeks in the centre before
OL,21,Fbeing released.
